  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Clean Water for 1,500 Children in Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">20 million Ugandans lack access to clean water, leading to easily preventable diseases. Among those most at risk are children, whose developing immune systems can&apos;t handle the physical stress imposed by COVID-19, malnutrition, and waterborne diseases (the #2 killer of children). We will install our Purifaaya filter, which eliminates 99.9% of bacteria from water, and our handiClean handwashing station, in three schools in the District of Mityana, impacting 1,500 children and their families.</narrative>
  </description>
